{"name": "rox-icu", "metadata": {"name": "rox-icu", "version": "2.0.0", "classifiers": ["Development Status :: 3 - Alpha", "Intended Audience :: Developers", "Operating System :: OS Independent", "Programming Language :: Python", "Programming Language :: Python :: 3.11", "Topic :: Software Development :: Libraries :: Python Modules", "Typing :: Typed"], "home_page": null, "license": "MIT", "documentation_url": null, "dependencies": ["aiomqtt", "click", "coloredlogs", "orjson", "python-can"], "summary": "Integrated control unit", "upload_time": 1732983527}, "documentation": ["# ROX-ICU python driver\n\n\nThis package provides a high-level interface to ROX Integrated Control Unit.\n\nFor more information see [product page](https://roxautomation.com/icu.html)\n\n\n### Cli\n\nThe package installs `icu` command line tool with fuctional commands\n\n```\n  mock     Mock ICU device on CAN bus\n  monitor  Monitor ICU devices on CAN bus\n  output   Set output state, provide hex value\n```\n\n\n## Quick start\n\n```python\n\nimport asyncio\nimport logging\n\nfrom rox_icu.core import ICU\nfrom rox_icu.utils import run_main_async\n\nNODE_ID = 1\n\nSENSOR_PIN = 7\nRELAY_PIN = 0\n\nlog = logging.getLogger(\"main\")\n\n\nasync def handle_input(icu: ICU) -> None:\n    log.info(\"Starting input handler\")\n\n    sensor = icu.pins[SENSOR_PIN]\n    relay = icu.pins[RELAY_PIN]\n    relay.state = False\n\n    while True:\n        log.info(\"Waiting for high state\")\n        await sensor.high_event.wait()\n        log.info(f\"Sensor state: {sensor.state}\")\n\n        # toggle relay\n        relay.state = True\n        await asyncio.sleep(0.1)\n        relay.state = False\n\n\nasync def main() -> None:\n\n    icu = ICU(NODE_ID)\n    await icu.start()\n\n    try:\n        await handle_input(icu)\n    finally:\n        await icu.stop()\n        print(\"Done\")\n\n\nif __name__ == \"__main__\":\n    run_main_async(main())\n\n```\n"], "modules": [{"name": "rox_icu.bit_ops", "documentation": [], "functions": [{"name": "rox_icu.bit_ops.set_bit", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "value", "type": {"name": "int", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.int", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "default": null}, {"name": "bit", "type": {"name": "int", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.int", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "default": null}], "returns": {"name": "int", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.int", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "documentation": ["set bit in value"]}, {"name": "rox_icu.bit_ops.clear_bit", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "value", "type": {"name": "int", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.int", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "default": null}, {"name": "bit", "type": {"name": "int", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.int", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "default": null}], "returns": {"name": "int", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.int", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "documentation": ["clear bit in value"]}], "variables": [], "classes": [], "exports": []}, {"name": "rox_icu.can_utils", "documentation": ["supporting functions for working with can\n\nCopyright (c) 2024 ROX Automation - Jev Kuznetsov", "!/usr/bin/env python3"], "functions": [{"name": "rox_icu.can_utils.is_ci_environment", "asynchronous": false, "params": [], "returns": {"name": "bool", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.bool", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "documentation": ["Check if the code is running in a CI environment"]}, {"name": "rox_icu.can_utils.get_can_bus", "asynchronous": false, "params": [], "returns": {"name": "UdpMulticastBus | SocketcanBus", "xref": null, "params": null}, "documentation": ["Get a CAN bus instance, using environment variables\nCAN_CHANNEL and CAN_INTERFACE for configuration or a multicast bus in CI"]}], "variables": [], "classes": [], "exports": []}, {"name": "rox_icu.examples.wait_and_toggle", "documentation": ["example of waiting for an edge on input and toggling an output with a delay\n\nCopyright (c) 2024 ROX Automation - Jev Kuznetsov", "!/usr/bin/env python3"], "functions": [{"name": "rox_icu.examples.wait_and_toggle.handle_input", "asynchronous": true, "params": [{"name": "icu", "type": {"name": "ICU", "xref": {"fqname": "rox_icu.core.ICU", "project": null}, "params": null}, "default": null}], "returns": {"name": "None", "xref": {"fqname": "constants.None", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "documentation": []}, {"name": "rox_icu.examples.wait_and_toggle.main", "asynchronous": true, "params": [], "returns": {"name": "None", "xref": {"fqname": "constants.None", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "documentation": []}], "variables": [{"name": "rox_icu.examples.wait_and_toggle.NODE_ID", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "rox_icu.examples.wait_and_toggle.SENSOR_PIN", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "rox_icu.examples.wait_and_toggle.RELAY_PIN", "type": null, "documentation": []}, {"name": "rox_icu.examples.wait_and_toggle.log", "type": null, "documentation": []}], "classes": [], "exports": []}, {"name": "rox_icu.can_protocol", "documentation": ["ROX-ICU CAN Protocol Implementation\n\nWorks both in MicroPython and CPython.\n\nKey Features:\n-------------\n- Compatible with fixed-length and variable-length message formats.\n- Dynamic support for parameter-based messages, with `ParameterMessage`.\n- Uses an 11-bit structured message ID for efficient communication:\n  - Upper 6 bits: Node ID (0-63, with 0 reserved for broadcast)\n  - Lower 5 bits: Command ID (0-31)\n\nMessage Types:\n--------------\n- **HaltMessage**: Halts operations with a specific IO state.\n- **HeartbeatMessage**: Provides periodic status updates, including device type, IO state, errors, and a counter.\n- **IoStateMessage**: Reports or sets IO state changes.\n- **ParameterMessage**: Handles parameter updates or retrievals using a flexible format.\n\nAdding Custom Messages:\n-----------------------\n1. Define the message using a `namedtuple` or a custom class.\n2. Register the message type in the `_MSG_DEFS` dictionary with an associated opcode and format.\n3. Define the data structure using `struct` format characters (e.g., `B=uint8`, `H=uint16`).", "!/usr/bin/env python3", "Copyright (c) 2024 ROX Automation - Jev Kuznetsov"], "functions": [{"name": "rox_icu.can_protocol.generate_message_id", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "node_id", "type": {"name": "int", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.int", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "default": null}, {"name": "opcode", "type": {"name": "int", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.int", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "default": null}], "returns": {"name": "int", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.int", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "documentation": ["Generates an 11-bit message ID from opcode and node ID.", "----------------------------Utility Functions----------------------------"]}, {"name": "rox_icu.can_protocol.split_message_id", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "message_id", "type": {"name": "int", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.int", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "default": null}], "returns": {"name": "tuple", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.tuple", "project": "--std--"}, "params": [{"name": "int", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.int", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, {"name": "int", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.int", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}]}, "documentation": ["Splits a 11-bit message ID into opcode and node ID."]}, {"name": "rox_icu.can_protocol.get_node_id", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "message_id", "type": {"name": "int", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.int", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "default": null}], "returns": {"name": "int", "xref": {"fqname": "functions.int", "project": "--std--"}, "params": null}, "documentation": ["Get the node ID from a message ID."]}, {"name": "rox_icu.can_protocol.get_opcode_and_bytedef", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "message_class", "ty